&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Iran War:&lt;/strong&gt; Tensions in the Gulf escalated sharply on Thursday after Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) announced a series of drone attacks targeting American military facilities in Bahrain and Kuwait, while also declaring the strategic Strait of Hormuz closed to maritime traffic. The announcement came hours after fresh U.S. military operations inside Iran, marking another significant escalation in the confrontation between Washington and Tehran.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;IRGC Claims Strikes On Military Installations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In a statement, the IRGC said it had launched drone attacks against several military sites used by American forces in the Gulf region. Among the locations named were Bahrain&amp;rsquo;s Sheikh Isa airbase and Kuwait&amp;rsquo;s Ali Al Salem and Ahmad Al-Jaber airbases.&lt;/p&gt;
