&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump On Inflation:&lt;/strong&gt; President Donald Trump dismissed growing concerns over rising prices on Wednesday, arguing that inflationary pressures were temporary and closely tied to the ongoing conflict with Iran. Speaking to reporters after fresh economic data showed consumer prices increasing at their fastest pace in three years, Trump maintained that the situation would improve significantly once hostilities in the Middle East come to an end.&lt;/p&gt;
